It's Digvijaya brother vs Sushma in Vidisha
BHOPAL: In a late night decision Congress general secretary Digvijaya Singh's brother Laxman Singh has been fielded from Vidisha, to contest against Sushma Swaraj.
Swaraj is sitting BJP MP from this seat.
Earlier, state Congress had suggested party high command that Digvijaya be fielded against Swaraj. Talking to TOI, Singh said, "I am ready for the battle and will win."
Meanwhile, BJP has fielded Bodh Singh Bhagat from Balaghat constituency. Bhagat who belongs to Pawar community, is a former MLA from Waraseoni assembly seat in Balaghat and is vice-president of the state unit Bharatiya Kisan Sangh.

